The point you just made in your last post, and the point I've been trying to drive the whole time is drastically different.<br>
<br>
I'm not talking about exping in PoTactics or the Elemental Planes.  I'm talking about exping and obtaining some spell turn-ins from places like BoT, HoH and CoD.  <br>
<br>
My guild has taken the time to farm minis in PoS and many of our members are BoT flagged, including myself.  I enjoy exping there when I can get a group or when the right combination of guildmembers happens to be on and free.<br>
<br>
I would like to experience HoH and CoD as well.  Would my ability to exp in CoD and HoH be any different whether I killed Grummus and Aerin'Dar, or did the quests?  No, but that goes both ways.  If you want to impose rotations on Aerin'Dar and Grummus so that our whole guild has to do those stupid quests, then by all means go ahead.  Everyone can just suck it up and complete the quests.  I don't see what would be so horrible about 2 guilds in a 30/30 split killing Grummus thus letting 30 of thier members avoid wasting their time farming larvae in PoD.  <br>
